<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="110" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,834,2011]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,978,1003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
In the male genitalia, the set of three very large cornuti distinguishes 
<taxonomicName box="[1109,1241,979,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tripartita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1109,1241,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">S. tripartita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1248,1339,978,1003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1248,1339,978,1003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
from all other 
<taxonomicName box="[215,320,1014,1039]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[215,320,1014,1039]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Stigmella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species; the host-plant (
<taxonomicName box="[592,812,1014,1039]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Baccharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="buxifolia">
<emphasis box="[592,812,1014,1039]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Baccharis buxifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) also makes this species distinctive.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="110" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,834,2011]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1050,1075]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[275,359,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 38" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1551,1574]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,195,1520]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,195,1530]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 38. Stigmella tripartita Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 33, habitat, SW of Cajabamba, Chimborazo Province, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 3870 m; 34, 36, host-plant Baccharis buxifolia (Lam.) Pers.; 35, usual habitat of the species occurrence along roadsides; 37, cocoon; 38, forewing (reconstructed)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261794/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Fig. 
<number box="[327,359,1051,1075]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="38.0">38</number>
</figureCitation>
). Forewing length about 3.0 mm; wingspan about 6.5 mm (n= 
<number box="[1060,1075,1051,1075]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="2.0">2</number>
). Head: palpi cream; frontal tuft brown to brown cream; scape cream to yellowish cream; antenna longer than half the length of forewing; flagellum with approx. 
<number box="[309,337,1122,1147]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="26.0">26</number>
segments, grey.Thorax and tegula dark grey-brown to fuscous. Forewing dark brown-grey to fuscous, with slightly postmedian fascia; fascia broad to narrow, whitish grey or grey cream; terminal and tornal cilia pale grey-brown. Abdomen dark grey to fuscous (also see Remarks).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,834,2011]" box="[199,418,1230,1255]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1230,1255]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,834,2011]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,368,1266,1291]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[383,514,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1896,1919]" captionTargetBox="[190,1429,384,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,373,1876]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Male genitalia of Stigmella tripartita Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. (ZMUC). 39, capsule (without phallus), ventral view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 40, phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624; 41, capsule, dorsal view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 42, same, phallus; 43, capsule with phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261795/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Figs 
<number box="[440,514,1267,1291]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="41.0" valueMax="43.0" valueMin="39.0">39–43</number>
</figureCitation>
). Capsule short (
<number box="[700,800,1266,1291]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="262.5" valueMax="295.0" valueMin="230.0">230–295</number>
µm) but broad (
<number box="[979,1079,1266,1291]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="237.5" valueMax="240.0" valueMin="235.0">235–240</number>
µm). Vinculum with very small (
<number box="[159,230,1302,1327]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="27.5" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="25.0">25–30</number>
µm), triangularly shaped lateral (anterior) lobes; ventral plate of vinculum short. Uncus 
<number box="[1241,1312,1302,1327]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="87.5" valueMax="90.0" valueMin="85.0">85–90</number>
µm broad, with two small lobes, each bearing one (
<figureCitation box="[641,728,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1896,1919]" captionTargetBox="[190,1429,384,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,373,1876]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Male genitalia of Stigmella tripartita Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. (ZMUC). 39, capsule (without phallus), ventral view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 40, phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624; 41, capsule, dorsal view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 42, same, phallus; 43, capsule with phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261795/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Fig. 
<number box="[699,728,1339,1363]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
) or two papillae. Gnathos stout, with two caudal processes broadening basally (
<figureCitation box="[380,464,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1896,1919]" captionTargetBox="[190,1429,384,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,373,1876]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Male genitalia of Stigmella tripartita Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. (ZMUC). 39, capsule (without phallus), ventral view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 40, phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624; 41, capsule, dorsal view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 42, same, phallus; 43, capsule with phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261795/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Fig. 
<number box="[433,464,1375,1399]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
); central plate of gnathos large to very large, 
<number box="[980,1008,1374,1399]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="85.0">85</number>
µm broad, in the form of a trapezium (
<figureCitation box="[159,246,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1896,1919]" captionTargetBox="[190,1429,384,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,373,1876]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Male genitalia of Stigmella tripartita Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. (ZMUC). 39, capsule (without phallus), ventral view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 40, phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624; 41, capsule, dorsal view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 42, same, phallus; 43, capsule with phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261795/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Fig. 
<number box="[215,246,1411,1435]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
). Valva (
<figureCitation box="[352,436,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1896,1919]" captionTargetBox="[190,1429,384,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,373,1876]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Male genitalia of Stigmella tripartita Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. (ZMUC). 39, capsule (without phallus), ventral view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 40, phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624; 41, capsule, dorsal view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 42, same, phallus; 43, capsule with phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261795/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Fig. 
<number box="[407,436,1411,1435]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="39.0">39</number>
</figureCitation>
) 
<number box="[455,497,1411,1435]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="180.0">180</number>
µm long, 
<number box="[622,692,1410,1435]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="82.5" valueMax="85.0" valueMin="80.0">80–85</number>
µm broad, with two apical processes (ventral process short and pointed); inner lobe almost straight or slightly bulged; transtilla with rounded sublateral processes or without processes, rounded at corners (
<figureCitation box="[493,623,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1896,1919]" captionTargetBox="[190,1429,384,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,373,1876]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Male genitalia of Stigmella tripartita Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. (ZMUC). 39, capsule (without phallus), ventral view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 40, phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624; 41, capsule, dorsal view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 42, same, phallus; 43, capsule with phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261795/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Figs 
<number box="[549,623,1483,1507]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="41.43">41, 43</number>
</figureCitation>
). Juxta membranous, distinctly triangular, broadening caudally (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1424,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1896,1919]" captionTargetBox="[190,1429,384,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,373,1876]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Male genitalia of Stigmella tripartita Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. (ZMUC). 39, capsule (without phallus), ventral view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 40, phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624; 41, capsule, dorsal view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 42, same, phallus; 43, capsule with phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261795/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1424,1483,1507]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="39.0">39</number>
</figureCitation>
). Phallus (
<figureCitation box="[249,420,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1896,1919]" captionTargetBox="[190,1429,384,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,373,1876]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Male genitalia of Stigmella tripartita Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. (ZMUC). 39, capsule (without phallus), ventral view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 40, phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624; 41, capsule, dorsal view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 42, same, phallus; 43, capsule with phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261795/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Figs 
<number box="[306,379,1519,1543]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="40.42">40, 42</number>
, 
<number box="[391,420,1519,1543]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="43.0">43</number>
</figureCitation>
) very short (
<number box="[565,664,1518,1543]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="172.5" valueMax="200.0" valueMin="145.0">145–200</number>
µm) but broad (
<number box="[848,891,1519,1543]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="120.0">120</number>
µm); vesica with a set of three very large (up to 
<number box="[151,193,1555,1579]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="100.0">100</number>
µm long) cornuti (
<figureCitation box="[404,489,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1896,1919]" captionTargetBox="[190,1429,384,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,373,1876]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Male genitalia of Stigmella tripartita Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. (ZMUC). 39, capsule (without phallus), ventral view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 40, phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624; 41, capsule, dorsal view, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 622; 42, same, phallus; 43, capsule with phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 624." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261795/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Fig. 
<number box="[457,489,1555,1579]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="40.0">40</number>
</figureCitation>
); no small spinose cornuti developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,834,2011]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,330,1590,1615]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Bionomics.</emphasis>
Larvae mine in leaves. Host-plant: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lam.) Pers." authorityName="(Lam.) Pers." box="[746,1120,1590,1615]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Baccharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="buxifolia">
<emphasis box="[746,969,1590,1615]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Baccharis buxifolia</emphasis>
(Lam.) 
<collectingCountry box="[1064,1116,1591,1614]" name="Iran" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Pers</collectingCountry>
.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1136,1262,1591,1615]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1288,1424,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 38" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1551,1574]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,195,1520]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,195,1530]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 38. Stigmella tripartita Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 33, habitat, SW of Cajabamba, Chimborazo Province, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 3870 m; 34, 36, host-plant Baccharis buxifolia (Lam.) Pers.; 35, usual habitat of the species occurrence along roadsides; 37, cocoon; 38, forewing (reconstructed)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261794/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Figs 
<number box="[1347,1424,1590,1615]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="34.36">34, 36</number>
</figureCitation>
). Larvae yellow to pale yellow, and mine in February. Contorted gallery of mine with central line of dark brown to black frass (approximately resembling the mines of the European 
<taxonomicName authority="Stt." authorityName="Stt." box="[890,1103,1662,1687]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myrtilella">
<emphasis box="[890,1027,1662,1687]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">S. myrtilella</emphasis>
(Stt.))
</taxonomicName>
. Larval exit slit on upper side of the leaf. Cocoon grey-beige to grey-ochre; length 2.6–3.2 mm, maximal width 1.3–1.8 mm (
<figureCitation box="[1253,1340,1698,1723]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 38" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1551,1574]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,195,1520]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,195,1530]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 38. Stigmella tripartita Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 33, habitat, SW of Cajabamba, Chimborazo Province, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 3870 m; 34, 36, host-plant Baccharis buxifolia (Lam.) Pers.; 35, usual habitat of the species occurrence along roadsides; 37, cocoon; 38, forewing (reconstructed)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261794/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Fig. 
<number box="[1308,1340,1699,1723]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="37.0">37</number>
</figureCitation>
). Adults emerged in March.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="110" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,834,2011]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1770,1795]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[362,431,1770,1795]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1980,2002]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1956]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1959]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 3. Current records of Stigmella species feeding on plants from the genus Baccharis L." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261788/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Fig. 
<number box="[415,431,1771,1795]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). This species occurs high in the equatorial Andes (
<collectingCountry box="[1020,1117,1770,1795]" name="Ecuador" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
) at altitudes between 
<quantity metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.835" metricValueMax="3.87" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" unit="m" value="3835.0" valueMax="3870.0" valueMin="3800.0">3800– 3870 m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[251,334,1806,1831]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 38" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1551,1574]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,195,1520]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,195,1530]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 38. Stigmella tripartita Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 33, habitat, SW of Cajabamba, Chimborazo Province, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 3870 m; 34, 36, host-plant Baccharis buxifolia (Lam.) Pers.; 35, usual habitat of the species occurrence along roadsides; 37, cocoon; 38, forewing (reconstructed)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261794/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Fig. 
<number box="[303,334,1807,1831]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
), mostly along roadsides (
<figureCitation box="[628,712,1806,1831]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 38" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1551,1574]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,195,1520]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,195,1530]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 38. Stigmella tripartita Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 33, habitat, SW of Cajabamba, Chimborazo Province, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 3870 m; 34, 36, host-plant Baccharis buxifolia (Lam.) Pers.; 35, usual habitat of the species occurrence along roadsides; 37, cocoon; 38, forewing (reconstructed)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261794/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
Fig. 
<number box="[680,712,1806,1831]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="35.0">35</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="110" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,834,2011]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1842,1867]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[840,954,1844,1867]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">tripartitus</emphasis>
(divided in three parts; triple) in reference to the unusual set of three very large cornuti of the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="110" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,834,2011]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1914,1939]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Remarks</emphasis>
. This distinctive new species, associated with 
<taxonomicName box="[853,1077,1914,1939]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Baccharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="buxifolia">
<emphasis box="[853,1077,1914,1939]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Baccharis buxifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a host-plant and possessing three large cornuti in the male genitalia, is described from the genitalia slides dissected from adults still enclosed within the pupa shell.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
